article.headline: Seattle wins 86-79 against Grand Canyon

images.name: Grand Canyon Antelopes vs. Seattle U Redhawks: Full Highlights
images.caption: Grand Canyon Antelopes vs. Seattle U Redhawks: Full Highlights

article.story: SEATTLE -- — Cameron Tyson scored 25 points as Seattle beat Grand Canyon 86-79 on Saturday night. Tyson shot 6 for 11 (5 for 8 from 3-point range) and 8 of 10 from the free-throw line for the Redhawks (11-8, 4-4 Western Athletic Conference). John Christofilis added 15 points while shooting 5 for 11 (2 for 7 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line, and they also had five rebounds. Kobe Williamson had 15 points and went 6 of 7 from the field. Gabe McGlothan finished with 28 points, seven rebounds and four steals for the Antelopes (17-2, 7-1). Tyon Grant-Foster added 25 points and seven rebounds for Grand Canyon. In addition, Rayshon Harrison had 11 points. The loss broke the Antelopes' 14-game winning streak. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
